@HuntedOlesser  

Actually, not strictly better than [Black Cat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Black Cat). Black Cat causes random card discard which is significantly better than your opponent having the ability to choose. That and you cant' factor out the Cat's creature type either which is more relevant as a zombie. While yes, [Ashen-Skin Zubera](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ashen-Skin Zubera) is better in a dedicated Zubera deck, [Black Cat](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Black Cat) is better in a deck just splashing discard as an alternative to [Ravenous Rats](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ravenous Rats) or as a solid two tap in a Specter Deck. All on preference though.  

Anyways, solid card. I have a casual 5 color Zubera deck with nothing that's higher than a 2 drop. Just draw and drop Zuberas and drop the occasional fog and/or [Pyroclasm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pyroclasm) :D Definitely not competitive, but great fun casual deck. People debate swinging at me in multiplayer games :)

